        <style type="text/css">
            .parent {
                position: absolute;
                z-index: 1;
                background: #0FF;
                width: 120px;
                height: 120px;
            }
            .child {
                background: #0F0;
                width: 100px;
                height: 100px;
                margin: 10px;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if you can see a lime square with aqua borders.<br />
            If the borders are red, the test fails.</p>
        <div class="parent">
            <div class="child"></div>
        </div>
    

